The paper deals with the generation of realistic human videos, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain. The proposed model uses a GAN architecture, which involves training a generator to produce realistic videos, and this falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) domains. The paper also involves analyzing and comparing the performance of the proposed model with state-of-the-art methods, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) domains.
